{"questionId":"32400305","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Althea calculates the expected frequencies and records them in this table.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/228dd6ec55895ac467a5aaa44f318530f7da4d1d.png\" width=\"573\" height=\"82\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>state the value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></math></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>Since&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mo>→</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mo>∞</mo></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Accept equivalent reasoning in words, e.g. the fish will stop growing.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32400305","referenceCode":"24N.3.AHL.TZ0.2fii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"state the value of dLdt as t→∞","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.14—Setting up a DE, solve by separating variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
